  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The rest said, let be,.... The others, to whom he belonged, that fetched the sponge, said to him, let him alone, keep at a distance from him, give him nothing to drink: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "let us see whether Elias will come to save him; whom the Jews looked upon to be the forerunner of the Messiah, and therefore suggest, that should he come to save him, they would believe he was the Messiah; and they had a mighty notion of Elias appearing to persons frequently (s), and talking, and conversing with them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See Gill on Matthew 17:3, though they did not believe he would come, and appear to Christ; for they were persons of great note for piety and learning, to whom he appeared, as they pretend, whereas they had no such opinion of him. The Ethiopic version here adds, and one took a spear and pierced his side with it, and blood and water flowed out: but this circumstance is only recorded by the Evangelist John, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 17:3",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", though they did not believe he would come, and appear to Christ; for they were persons of great note for piety and learning, to whom he appeared, as they pretend, whereas they had no such opinion of him. The Ethiopic version here adds, and one took a spear and pierced his side with it, and blood and water flowed out: but this circumstance is only recorded by the Evangelist John, ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "John 19:34, though Beza says the same is read here in two ancient copies, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 19:34",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", though Beza says the same is read here in two ancient copies, ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(s) Vid. Juchasin, fol. 79. 1. & 86. 1. & 101. 1. & 118. 2. & 132. 1.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(s) Vid. Juchasin, fol. 79. 1. & 86. 1. & 101. 1. & 118. 2. & 132. 1.",
            "children": []
